📌 What is Amazon RDS?
            Amazon RDS (Relational Database Service) is a fully managed AWS service that makes it easy to set up, 
            operate, and scale a relational database in the cloud. AWS handles all the heavy lifting 
            — backups, patching, scaling, and high availability.
🗄️ Part 1 — Create the Database:
Step 1 — Navigate:

Go to AWS Console → Search "RDS" → Click "RDS"
In the left panel → Click "Databases"
Click "Create Database" ✅
